A
THEORY
OF
RADAR
REFLECTION
FROM
THE
MOON
AND
PLANETS
RELATIONS
BETWEEN
THE
SURFACE
STATISTICS
OF
AN
IRREGULAR
RADAR
TARGET
AND
THE
ANGULAR
POWER
SPECTRUM
AND
AUTOCORRELATION
FUNCTION
OF
THE
REFLECTED
SIGNAL
ARE
DERIVED
THE
SPATIAL
CORRELATION
FUNCTION
IS
ALSO
COMPUTED
THE
THEORY
IS
USED
TO
INVESTIGATE
THE
SMALL
SCALE
STRUCTURE
OF
THE
MOONS
SURFACE
